Source: minic
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: MiniC Developers <dev@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), cmake, g++
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Homepage: https://github.com/example/minic

Package: minic
Architecture: any
Depends: gcc, gcc-multilib, libc6-dev-i386, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A minimal subset C compiler producing x86-32 assembly.
 minic is a professional, portable compiler for a minimal subset of the C
 programming language. It performs all standard compiler phases, from
 lexical analysis to x86-32 assembly code generation.
